{
  "doc_id": "41945",
  "text": "Animals: Adult, male Sprague-Dawley rats weighing approximately 320 g from a local breeding colony (Biomedical Centre, Uppsala University, Uppsala, Sweden) were used in all experiments. The animals had free access to pelleted rat food (Type R3; Ewos AB, Page 4 of 25 [CITATION_1] Sollentuna, Sweden) and tap water until the night before the experiments, when food was withdrawn. The animals were divided into twelve groups. Two groups received each pretreatment as outlined below and one group in each pair was subjected to hypothermia, while the other group was investigated at normothermia. The experiments were reviewed and approved by the Uppsala municipal court animal research ethics commitee.",
